\section{Performing one step interaction}

The step model only carries one interaction switch: if [[edit_file]] is
set, the runner opens that file in an editor.  Otherwise it falls back to
the existing shell session.

Nested tutorials want the shell prompt to include the tutorial name.  The
built-in shell backends can accept that prompt name, but injected test or
host runners may still only accept [[workspace]].  A small adapter keeps
that compatibility check in one place.

<<functions>>=
def run_step_shell(
    shell_runner: Callable[..., ShellResult],
    *,
    workspace: str | Path,
    tutorial_id: str,
) -> ShellResult:
    """Run one shell step, passing a prompt name when supported."""

    try:
        parameters = inspect.signature(shell_runner).parameters.values()
    except (TypeError, ValueError):
        return shell_runner(workspace=workspace)

    accepts_prompt_name = any(
        parameter.kind == inspect.Parameter.VAR_KEYWORD
        or parameter.name == "prompt_name"
        for parameter in parameters
    )
    if accepts_prompt_name:
        return shell_runner(
            workspace=workspace,
            prompt_name=tutorial_id,
        )
    return shell_runner(workspace=workspace)
@

