and persistence policy rather than on backend selection.  Question steps
still reuse the same persisted transcript shape; they just obtain that
recorded text from a prompt callback instead of from a shell or editor.

<<functions>>=
def missing_question_runner(*, step: TutorialStep) -> ShellResult:
    """Fail clearly when question steps reach a runner without prompt support."""

    raise RuntimeError(
        f"Step {step.title!r} uses question kind {step_kind(step)!r}, "
        "but no question runner was configured."
    )
